{
  "texts": [
    "Notice that the decomposition T B = T B0 ⊕ • • • ⊕ T Br is orthogonal for h * g sym by (20b).",
    "Moreover, on each Bi, i > 0, we have h * g sym = c i g B for some c i > 0 since h * g sym is parallel and the holonomy acts irreducibly on T Bi.",
    "The restriction of h * g sym to B0 is a Euclidean metric, so up to isometry we may assume that h * g sym agrees with g0 on B0.",
    "Hence, h * g sym is complete, being the Riemannian product of complete metrics.Therefore, by [Hel78, Thm.",
    "IV.7.2], B ⊂ G/K is the orbit of a connected reductive subgroup G ′ ≤ G. Since G ′ is connected, it preserves the irreducible components of B."
  ]
}